creator: Anna Katharine Green
description:
LibriVox recording of One of My Sons by Anna Katharine Green.
Read by Laura Victoria
A young girl frantically summons a gentleman walking by on the street to come in and help her grandfather. Arthur Outhwaite answers her cry for help only to find himself as the last person to see her grandfather alive and left with the admonishment from the dying man to deliver a letter to someone, and to that person only. Unfortunately, he dies before he can inform Outhwaite who that particular person is. Being in a house of strangers, Outhwaite is thrust into the mystery of not only finding this unknown person, but is also faced with the mysterious circumstances under which the child's grandfather died. (Summary by Laura Victoria)
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

reviews.reviewbody:
The plot was interesting, although a bit obvious at times.

The reading by Laura Victoria was excellent. 

I would probably give the story 4 stars, but must give more based on the quality of the recording.
